The Main Page.

Jenton provided this useful insight into Eve-talk in the forum, with Gandur adding some mining specific abbreviations.

AB
 Afterburner
AF
 Assualt Frigate
Apoc
 Apocalypse
AR
 Armor Repair
Ark
 Arkonor (also known as the HOLY GRAIL of ores)
Arty
 Artillery, type of projectile gun
Ares
 Tech 2 Shuttle
BC
 Battle Cruiser
BCU
 Ballistic Control Unit
Bis
 Bistot
BP
 Blue Print
BPC
 Blueprint Copy
BPO
 Blue Print Original, worth fortunes
BS
 Battleship
Cap
 Capacitor
Carebear
 Anyone who fits WCS
Carebear
 Player who doesnt pvp
CR
 Capacitor Recharger
CR
 Cruiser
CPR
 Capacitor Power Relay
CPU
 Central Processing Unit, Co-processor
Crok
 Crokite
DC
 Damage Control
DO
 Dark Ochre
DPS
 Damage Per Second
ECM
 Electronic Counter Measure
ECCM
 Electronic Counter Counter Measure
EW
 Electronic Warfare
Frig
 Frigate
Geddon
 Armmageddon
Grid
 Power Grid
HAC
 Heavy assualt ships (heavy assualt "cruisers" like cerberus)
Hauler
 Industrial ships (like badger or iterons)
Hardner
 Module that increases resistance for shield or armor
Harvies
 Harvester Mining Drones
Hed
 Hedbergite
Indy
 An industrial ship
Intie
 Interceptors
MAPC
 Micro Auxilary Power Core
Mega
 Megathron
Mod
 Module
MWD
 Micro Warp Drive
Neut
 Capacitor Neutralizer
Nos
 Nosferatu, a module that will drain the target ships power
Optimal
 Your optimal range
PDU
 Power Diagnostic System
Plag
 Plagioclase
Plate
 Armor increasing item like a 1600mm armor plate
Phoon
 Typhoon
Pod
 To blow up someone's capsule
POS
 Player Owned Station
PvP
 Player vs Player
Pyr
 Pyroxeres
QFT
 Quoted For Truth
Rat
 NPCs that will attack anyone. Threat level depends on Security Status of the system
RCU
 Reactor Control Unit
RoF
 Rate of Fire
SB
 Shield Booster / Sensor Booster / Smartbomb
SBA
 Shield Boost Amplifier
Scord
 Scordite
SP
 Skill Points
SPR
 Shield Power Relay
Strips
 Strip miners / exotic dancers from "damsel in distress" mission
Tackle
 To warp scramble and/or Web Stasify
T2
 Technology Level Two (Tech 2)
Veld
 Veldspar
WCS
 Warp Core Stabalizer
Web
 Stasis Webifier
